Entries.DialogueText: Hey, thanks a bunch, ! This makes my birthday feel special.
Oh! Thank you! This one has an interesting shape...
0.8Oh, wow, ! This is exactly what I was craving! How'd you know?
Mmm... Back in the city, the veggies never tasted this fresh. I love it!
Hey, where'd you find that? *sniff*... Mmm... This will be perfect, grated over a fresh pasta. Thank you!
Oh, wow... I had a sip of this stuff when I was a kid, and I've never forgotten the taste.
I came for the sound of the ocean. Beautiful, isn't it?
Ohh... Got it. Hah... I really don't have any luck when it comes to this stuff...
I had a feeling you would ask me...
Please don't feel like you have to spend all your time with me now that we're dating... I know you're a busy person!
I've realized I'm happier by myself. So just leave me be.
I don't want to see you for a while...
You're right... I just wouldn't have been happy back there.
It was better for both of us... to end an unsustainable relationship while we were still young and flexible.
That's a little harsh... but, yeah. We had different priorities.
Oh yeah? Well maybe I'll just leave, then!
*sigh*...
I guess you're right... it was kind of selfish. But can you really blame me for wanting to be happy? Ugh... I don't know...
Maybe you're right... Humans are selfish creatures. I don't know.
I probably shouldn't dwell on it. We all have to make hard choices from time to time.
...What?
Oh! Yeah, that's absolutely right!
There's nothing wrong with that... I think there's lots of beauty to be found in raw, untouched nature!
But as a human, I'm also interested in how we shape and interpret the world around us... I guess what I'm saying is that I'm interested in 'art'.
You pig!
Oh! You're...? Me too.
Get out!
That's good to know.
I sold enough art at that show to get by for another year... that's all I needed!
I'm still fuming about the picnic... what a weirdo!
Let's never talk about... that person... ever again.
If my art continues to sell online like it has, I'll be able to keep making art forever. That's always been my dream.
How quickly the seasons change!
It's shocking.
Do you have a kitchen in your house?
If you have a kitchen, you can cook all kinds of delicious meals.
Stop by my cabin if you ever need someone to talk to.
I found some wild mushrooms over the weekend!
I had a huge plate of wild mushrooms and eggs for breakfast today... I'm still full.
Keep your nose to the ground and you'll find some mushrooms yourself... I'm sure of it.
Decorations accentuate the feeling of the season. I think it's a worthwhile tradition.
There's a lot of good places to walk around here.
It feels good to stretch your legs.
One thing I love about this place is that there are beautiful waterfalls.
Do you ever spend time watching them? It's soothing...
One of these days I'll have to make you a wild mushroom stir-fry.
I wonder if I could make a collage out of dried leaves?
They're just so colorful... I can't help but think of the potential for art projects.
Everyone has a unique and interesting perspective, whether they believe it or not. Don't you think so?
Although, some people have opinions that I just can't respect.
It's so nice to live by the river.
I fall asleep to the soothing sound of water every night.
You want to dance with me? Yes!
I was wondering if you'd ask me...
Finally! I was starting to get worried you wanted to dance with someone else!
I'll be honest. I don't want to dance with you.
It's simpler to be friends with the trees. They don't have much to say.
We wouldn't be able to survive without nature. It's good to remember that.
Hello, . It's a nice day, isn't it?
Sometimes, a strange feeling comes over me. My head becomes totally empty... and I feel completely at peace, even blissful.
Hey, now! It has nothing to do with drinking wine!
Do you ever wonder what it's like to be a different person?
Do our thoughts manifest in a similar way, or is it radically different?
Don't mind me, I think about weird things sometimes...
Where did all these plants come from? It's a surprise, but I'm not complaining...
Imagine if this rain lasted all summer... The plants would take over the entire valley!
I guess everyone in town was scared of that strange rain? I had no idea... I just thought it was incredible!
Hello, it's nice to meet you.
You picked a good time to move here... The spring is lovely.
Elliott's a real romantic... I'm sure your days will be filled with poetry!
I'm happy that Shane's in such a good place. I've never seen him smile so much!
With his love for chickens, I'm sure he'll fit right in on Farm!

The trees look nice today, don't they?So why did you become a farmer?I want to make tons of money.It's more "real" than living in the city.To follow in Grandpa's footsteps.I wanted to escape my old life.
Hmm. That seems kind of shallow, doesn't it?
That's very sweet to honor your grandfather like that.
Hey... That's pretty much the reason I came here, too!
I wanted to connect with nature more...
21#So are you making as much money as you hoped?|Spending time in nature is very rewarding.
I love the weather in Stardew Valley, but seeing a different climate now and then helps put things into perspective.
Have you tried the Pi√±a Colada? I'm on my second one... hehe.
I like the heat as long as I'm keeping perfectly still.
Don't tell anyone, but Willy let me steer the boat for a few minutes.
Well, that was deeply relaxing.
The shape of the waves here is awe inspiring.
I wonder if I could ever capture that sort of formlessness in a sculpture.
Mmm, I bet the trees around here would make for an interesting medium to work with.
Though Willy probably wouldn't be happy with me if I dragged a bunch of logs onto his ship!
I wonder what kind of things you could forage out here.
I think I saw some tasty looking walnuts growing on a bush nearby.
I love to decorate for the different seasons.
I've thought about growing some crops, but I think I'd feel bad having to clear out all the wild plants to make space.|Farming sounds so fun. I want to try it, someday.
You caused a lot of grief with what you did... but I'm ready to put the past behind us.
You can tell it's summer by the sweet smell of nectar wafting through the air!
You can use a tapper to harvest syrups and other useful liquids directly from trees.
It's a slow process, but the result can be quite valuable.
I hate to be blunt, but if we don't treat nature with respect, our grandchildren will be doomed.
Don't you think so?
Do you ever walk out into the forest... Pause... And simply enjoy the beauty of nature?
It's easy to forget how incredible this world actually is...
Hello, . Do you ever get lonely on that big farm?
I found some wild fruits this morning!
Sorry, I don't have any left.
Keep looking, I'm sure you'll find something.
The flowing water keeps my house a little bit cooler in summer.
I can't tolerate heat very well.
One Summer, it was so hot during the night that I got out of bed and jumped into the river!
I hope no one saw me!
What should I do on such a warm, lazy day? *sigh*
Any ideas?
I have a good eye for wild fruit. Some day I'll make you a nice fruit salad.
The sound of farm animals is great, isn't it?
The simple things in life are best: a soft summer breeze, majestic clouds, and a goblet full of Stardew Valley red.
If you hear any banging from inside my hut, it's probably just me working on one of my sculptures.
If you ever find any interesting looking driftwood, I could use it.
It would be special that you gave it to me.
There's actually a lot of wild food in this area, if you know where to look.
I've been having fresh salads almost every day.
Foraging is a specialty of mine. Someday I'll make you a fresh salad.
Hello, neighbor.
We both live outside of town. Does that mean something?
Hi. Oh, you want to talk?
The landscape around here gives me a lot of ideas. The terrain is almost like a sculpture itself.
I don't make art for money. It's just an urge that I have.
Farming seems like a very rewarding profession. You get to create delicious food for everyone!
You're probably busy. Sorry.
This morning I accidentally stepped on a bug.
Sometimes I think it's impossible to live without destroying nature in some way.
I love being around animals. They're so innocent.
Farm animals are wonderful, too.
It must be satisfying to harvest a whole field of crops, huh? You're basically creating food out of nothing!|Hi ! I was just thinking about you and your farm.
I was imagining how good it must feel to harvest a big bunch of crops.
Wouldn't it be nice to have help, though?
Time seems to move slower here.
When I lived in the city, the year went by so fast.
Do you ever get cold in that farmhouse of yours?
Stop by my cabin if you want to huddle under one of my quilts and drink cider.
I love the way everything looks when it's covered with fresh snow.
Hello. Do you want something?
Hello, . Is there something you wanted to talk about?
Do you ever take a whole day off?
It's a refreshing break.
You should take a whole day off, now and then.
Not only is it good for the soul, but in the long run, you'll actually be more productive!
I'm having a hard time finding fresh food to eat.
I've been eating a lot of bread.
*Sigh*... It's hard to get fresh food in the winter.
I bet your farm is pretty well stocked with food, huh?
It gets pretty cold in my little cabin.
I just snuggle up under a huge blanket, and I'm okay.
I saw a snow rabbit early this morning! They're rare, aren't they?
I'm a little nervous. But happy.
I've always dreamed of living on a farm.
I'm going to be so happy.

Entries.DialogueFrom: Event:Farm/3911124/f Leah 3500/O Leah/t 500 820/w sunny/z winter/d Sun
Entries.DialogueText: Hey, . I have an idea...

Entries.DialogueFrom: Event:Farm/3911124/f Leah 3500/O Leah/t 500 820/w sunny/z winter/d Sun_1
Entries.DialogueText: I want you to meet me in Cindersap Forest tomorrow, at noon.

Entries.DialogueFrom: Event:Farm/3911124/f Leah 3500/O Leah/t 500 820/w sunny/z winter/d Sun_2
Entries.DialogueText: I'm gonna teach you how to paint!

Entries.DialogueFrom: Event:Farm/3911124/f Leah 3500/O Leah/t 500 820/w sunny/z winter/d Sun_1
Entries.DialogueText: If the weather's bad, we'll do it the next day. Okay?

Entries.DialogueFrom: Event:Farm/3911124/f Leah 3500/O Leah/t 500 820/w sunny/z winter/d Sun_implied
Entries.DialogueText: It'll be nice to explore your creative side a bit more, don't you think?
Hi ! Are you free this afternoon?
I finally got my act together and I'm doing my art show tonight in the town square!
Come into town between 3:00 and 5:00 pm if you want to be there!
I'm nervous...
Hi, . Beautiful day, isn't it?
I brought you a gift.
It's a sculpture I've been working on, just for you.
It's called... 'How I Feel About '. I hope you like it.
Just keep perfectly still, Marnie... No squirming!
Hey, ... what style do you think I should do? I'm up for anything...
How's yours coming along?
Now, don't forget the techniques I taught you... broad strokes, hold the brush like so...
Now, let's see what you've got, .
Erm... It's... interesting!
It's, uh... a different kind of approach, for sure...
Marnie, you can hang both of these in your room!
Shh!
There!
What do you think?
Stick with the classic look, huh? Yeah, I think Marnie will appreciate that.
Good idea! That sounds fun... Let me get some more yellow paint on the palette...
Hmm... not my usual style, but I'll give it a shot. I'd better switch to acrylic paint for this one...
Wow, I like your confidence!
Who knows? Maybe you'll become the next Lupini!
...Can't wait to see it.
Hey, that's all I ask. If you keep trying your best you can't help but get better at it!
Hey, that's okay! You gotta start somewhere. And you never know, one person's chicken scratch is another person's 'modern art'.
Oh! ! You scared me.
See that fruit up there? It looks delicious, doesn't it?
But I can't reach it.
Aghh!
Hehe...Thanks.
Okay... got it!
You're stronger than you look!
Here, try a piece...
You know, I just realized something.
Even if my art career is a flop, I'll always have a friend to catch me on the way down.
Thanks for helping me earlier...
Hi . I knew you'd be passing through here today.
...So I put together a surprise...
It's a little picnic for us!
Let's get out of here. I don't think Kel will be bothering us anymore.
Let's find a more secluded spot this time...
This is a vegetable medley, with my 'special' spice blend.
...and this is a fresh salad, made from greens that I foraged right here in the forest!
I just want to say thank you... for helping me get one step closer to becoming a real artist.
Kel??
What the heck are you doing here?
Yuck, don't call me that!
You never supported my art before... now that I've had some success you want me back? You make me sick.
Oh my God!
Well, he'll make it... but that was pretty violent, .
She's fine... but that was pretty violent, .
DISTANT VOICE: Well, well, well... What have we here?
KEL: Didn't you see me at the art show? I came all the way from Zuzu City to see your sculptures.
KEL: And to get you to come back with me.
KEL: I want things to go back to the way they were... I miss you, babe.
KEL: Hey! Come Here!
Try reasoning with Kel.
Well, the picnic didn't pan out like I wanted it to.
You're 'Mr. K'? I... I thought it was just a rich guy who truly loved my art.
Ew, don't call me that!
Well, he's fine... but that was pretty violent, .
KEL: Heh. Well, you were half right...
KEL: Look, Leah. I want you back. I miss you, babe.
's a better ${man
person}$ than you in every respect!
Now get out of here and never come back!
Let's go, . I don't think Kel will be bothering us anymore.

Entries.DialogueFrom: Event:HaleyHouse/195012/f Haley 2500/f Emily 2500/f Penny 2500/f Abigail 2500/f Leah 2500/f Maru 2500/o Abigail/o Penny/o Leah/o Emily/o Maru/o Haley/o Shane/o Harvey/o Sebastian/o Sam/o Elliott/o Alex/e 38/e 2123343/e 10/e 901756/e 54/e 15/k 195019
Entries.DialogueText: I... I thought you were different than other men...

Entries.DialogueFrom: Event:HaleyHouse/195012/f Haley 2500/f Emily 2500/f Penny 2500/f Abigail 2500/f Leah 2500/f Maru 2500/o Abigail/o Penny/o Leah/o Emily/o Maru/o Haley/o Shane/o Harvey/o Sebastian/o Sam/o Elliott/o Alex/e 38/e 2123343/e 10/e 901756/e 54/e 15/k 195019_1
Entries.DialogueText: You tricked all of us into thinking we loved you... You're horrible...

Entries.DialogueFrom: Event:HaleyHouse/195012/f Haley 2500/f Emily 2500/f Penny 2500/f Abigail 2500/f Leah 2500/f Maru 2500/o Abigail/o Penny/o Leah/o Emily/o Maru/o Haley/o Shane/o Harvey/o Sebastian/o Sam/o Elliott/o Alex/e 38/e 2123343/e 10/e 901756/e 54/e 15/k 195019_1
Entries.DialogueText: Absolutely.

Entries.DialogueFrom: Event:HaleyHouse/195012/f Haley 2500/f Emily 2500/f Penny 2500/f Abigail 2500/f Leah 2500/f Maru 2500/o Abigail/o Penny/o Leah/o Emily/o Maru/o Haley/o Shane/o Harvey/o Sebastian/o Sam/o Elliott/o Alex/e 38/e 2123343/e 10/e 901756/e 54/e 15/k 195019_alt
Entries.DialogueText: Stop!

Entries.DialogueFrom: Event:HaleyHouse/195012/f Haley 2500/f Emily 2500/f Penny 2500/f Abigail 2500/f Leah 2500/f Maru 2500/o Abigail/o Penny/o Leah/o Emily/o Maru/o Haley/o Shane/o Harvey/o Sebastian/o Sam/o Elliott/o Alex/e 38/e 2123343/e 10/e 901756/e 54/e 15/k 195019_alt_1
Entries.DialogueText: That's right!

Entries.DialogueFrom: Event:HaleyHouse/195019/f Haley 2500/f Emily 2500/f Penny 2500/f Abigail 2500/f Leah 2500/f Maru 2500/o Abigail/o Penny/o Leah/o Emily/o Maru/o Haley/o Shane/o Harvey/o Sebastian/o Sam/o Elliott/o Alex/e 38/e 2123343/e 10/e 901756/e 54/e 15/i 446/k 195012_alt
Entries.DialogueText: Look who it is!
Oh, hi ! Come in, come in.
I'm just working on this sculpture here.
Well, thanks for stopping by, .
Come here. Watch this.
See that? I'm revealing the essence of the wood.
-1 null -1 0 event_sculpt1 -1 0 event_sculpt2 -1 -100 event_sculpt3#(creepy) May I have a kiss?
I first visited this valley as a little girl, while on vacation with my parents.
I knew I had to come back some day... This place has great artistic potential!
Although, I have to admit... It's not easy to pay the bills as an artist.
Hmmm... interesting. I guess that could set the wheels in motion to making Pelican Town a true art destination...
But what if no one likes my sculptures? I'd be crushed.
...I'll have to think about it.
Why don't you sell your art on the internet?
An art show for the whole village? That's a bold idea, .
Kel...How many times do I have to tell you? I don't want to come back to the city!
Stop calling me... I don't want to hear from you anymore! *click*
So I guess you heard me yelling on the phone?
That was my ex...
I guess I'd better tell you a little about it...
We had an apartment together, back in the city.
I did odd jobs during the day and spent all night working on art projects... we barely made enough to scrape by.
${He
She}$ was always nagging me to go back to school and study business or medicine... something with a lot of money in it.
I guess the idea was to save up for a normal life. You know... a house in the suburbs, kids, PTA meetings... that sort of thing.
I wasn't ready for that kind of life, ... I had to leave. So I came here to pursue my dream of being an artist.
83 null 83 0 event_parents1 83 0 event_parents2 83 -20 event_parents3 83 -20 event_parents4 83 -20 event_parents5#Yeah, but it's natural to care about yourself first.
Well, thanks for listening to me. It's good to have a friend.
Hey, thanks for listening to me so patiently earlier.
Hey! Come check this out.
I bought a laptop and set up an online art shop... like you suggested.
Did you hear that? That means someone just bought something from the store!
Hmm... There's this 'Mr. K' that keeps buying all my sculptures.
I guess it must be some rich guy who loves my stuff.
Wow! I'm not going to have to worry about my electricity bill for a while after that sale...
Anyway... Thanks for giving me this idea, . So far, it's been really successful! This is really going to give me the funding I need to keep working on art full-time.
Now, sorry to ignore you... but I really need to tweak these CSS sheets...
Sorry... I shouldn't get angry.
Maybe you're right... my life would've been a lot easier if I had stayed.
Maybe it's better to be practical and realistic... for all I know my art career will never pan out and I'll live my final years in squalor.
Anyway... I've been thinking a little more about that art show idea you had.
I'm working on some new sculptures to display at the show... I'm nervous, but the thought of getting my work out there is pretty exciting.
I'm just glad you're on board with making Stardew Valley a premier art destination, !
Hmm... I guess that's an idea... But I'd need a computer first.
And again... that's expensive.
Well, it was nice of you to visit...
So I've been saving up money to buy a computer... You know, so I can try and sell my art online like you suggested.
It's good to have a friend looking out for you!
! You're here!
Okay... I guess I'd better introduce my pieces. Wish me luck!
Umm... Okay everyone!
I'd like to say thanks to my special friend, .
He gave me the idea for this show and the courage to go through with it. I know that sounds cheesy, but it's true.
She gave me the idea for this show and the courage to go through with it. I know that sounds cheesy, but it's true.
Thanks, everyone!
Thanks for coming to my art show.
As some of you know, I came to this town because I wanted to draw inspiration from the beautiful surroundings.
This place really feels like home now.
Okay. I'm going to introduce my sculptures now.
I haven't named this one, yet. She started out as an exercise in human anatomy, but I ended up seeing her through to completion.
Her expression is intentionally unclear... is she embarrassed, amused, pained? I'll leave that for you to decide.
This one's called 'Post-Dimensional Nullspace'. It represents the boundary of human imagination.
The shape and color came to me vividly when I was in a 'trance state'.
I've been calling this one 'Egg Heads'. I wanted to create an animatronic humanoid statue to toy with the viewer's ability to properly attribute personhood to a physical entity.
And the last one is called 'Wood Sculpture 3'. It's a celebration of my favorite sculpting material... wood.
Well, those are my sculptures!
Oh! One last thing.
The other day I bought {1} {2} at Pierre's. It was perfect on a bed of greens and a dash of my 'special' vinaigrette.
I think we've both found what we were looking for in this place.
I wouldn't want to be anywhere else, but here with you.
I learned all of Robin's techniques last year, but she's always one step ahead of me!
I really admire Robin's carpentry skills. I use a lot of the same techniques in my own line of work.
Hey, Robin is teaching me some innovative techniques this year.I'll have to show you later...
I think Robin and I make a pretty good team, don't you think?
I may have had a little too much pumpkin ale...
Mm, hi. Sorry... mouth full of blackberries.
I probably had too much pumpkin ale before jumping into the maze.You go on ahead. I'll catch up.
Is it this way? Or maybe over here?
I never had many friends in town, so these events are always kind of boring for me. I enjoy the buffet, though.
Mmmm... This fruit punch is unusually good.
Hmm... The punch isn't as good as last year. It's missing something!
Hi . Glad to see you here.
We should go hiking in these woods someday! I bet there's mushrooms...
I really feel connected with nature this far away from town.
It's nice to see everyone once in a while, but mostly I want to get back to the farm.
How's the farming coming along? It must be a busy season for you.
You better grab a plate before it's all gone!
I can't seem to decide what to eat! There's too many options to choose from.
Hey. I'm paying my respects to another bygone summer. I'll come meet up with you when we launch the candle-boat.
Hey. I'm paying my respects to another bygone summer.
I brought some sparkling wine for the main event... Summer's not over yet!
Have any fun plans for the fall season? I need to decorate my house soon.
I'm thankful for our simple life on the farm.
Gus was just telling me about his artisan candy canes. *yawn*I think he had too much cinnamon nog.
Elliott's drinking too much cider again...I'll come meet you at the table when I can find an exit... I'm starving!
Sometimes I dread going to parties, but afterwards I'm always glad I went!
Oh, ice. A beautiful material to sculpt in, but so impermanent.But I guess that might make the art even better.
Someday, I should teach you how to sculpt with ice! It would be fun!I'd be very curious to see what you'd come up with.
You have to temper ice before cutting it, otherwise you can't shape it!
Oh! This is exactly what I wanted! Thank you!
This is a really nice gift! Thank you!
Hmm... I guess everyone has different tastes.
This is a pretty terrible gift, isn't it?
Thank you.
